## Update payment settings

> Sample Request

```json
{
  "apiKey": "<%= config.auth %>",
  "billId": "566595c8ce88ccec69328566",
  "recurring": "enabled",
  "schedule": "five-days-before"
}
```

> 200 Response

```json
{
  "success": true
}
```

> 400 Response

```json
{
  "message": "Recurring payments may not be disabled for this company."
}
```

Update payment settings for a bill.

Some subscription companies, such as Netflix, Hulu, and Spotify require recurring payments to be enabled. If a request to the `/payment/settings` endpoint is made for one of these companies, a `400` status code will be returned and recurring payments will not be disabled.

### HTTP Request

`POST <%= config.host %>/payment/settings`

### Post Parameters

Param | Description
----- | -----------
`billId` | Unbill bill ID.
`recurring` | Whether recurring payments should be `enabled` or `disabled`.
`schedule` | The [bill payment schedule](#bill-payment-schedule) for payments

### Returns

Returns a `200` status code if settings were successfully updated.